This is Wall Power. And I=E2=80=99m Marion Maneker,
your regular guide through the art world demimonde.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Tonight, in the spirit of the New Year, I=E2=80=99m examining some themes I=
=E2=80=99ve divined in the barrage of year-launching art-market soothsaying=
=E2=80=94including two egregiously irresponsible predictions.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

But first=E2=80=A6

* Heritage Auctions posts record $1.9 billion in sales: A $6 million comic =
book; a $24 million baseball jersey worn by Babe Ruth; and a $32.5 million =
pair of movie-prop bedazzled =E2=80=9Cruby=E2=80=9D slippers that carried J=
udy Garland to Oz: These are the record sales figures for objects of cultur=
al importance sold last year by Dallas-based Heritage Auctions=E2=80=94the =
digitally innovative firm that began as a coin-auction house and has now be=
come a dominant player in the
auction market. They helped push the firm=E2=80=99s annual sales to a recor=
d $1.867 billion.

Heritage has been on such a growth tear, in fact, that it has more than dou=
bled its auction total in just four years, adding a billion in sales since =
the firm made $873 million in 2020. C.E.O. and co-founder Steve Ivy says en=
tertainment memorabilia grew by an explosive 2.5x year over year=E2=80=94in=
deed, these objects fetched the kinds of prices usually reserved for major =
works of art.
